       <header> <h1>Gabriel's Discussion Board </h1></header>
	   
	   <div class="r">
			<div class="column" style="background-color:#aaa;">
				<h2>Reason for Site</h2>
				<p> I love everything about the sport and would love to give my opinion on the games I watch. Oftentimes I feel that everyone just emphasizes the same points repeatedly, without adding much value. I hope add a different perspective that might vary from the norm. Furthermore, soccer is at a turning point. As the sport moves further into commertialization, there is a higher reliance on the finance side of the game. </p>
			</div>
			<div class="column" style="background-color:#bbb;">
			<h2>Latest News</h2>
				<article> 
					<img src="images/lewa.jpg" alt="lewa">
					<p> Rumors circulate about Lewandowski transfering to FC Barcelona. This would be one of the largest transfers of the year if it were to go through. The Polish striker currently wreaks havoc in the German Bundesliga League, scoring over 30 goals in a season consistenty. Even further, last eyar he broke the record for most goals in a single season with 41, breaking the longtime record set by Gerd Muller with his previous 40 goals. This could lead to one of the next largest transfers. If you want to hear about the others, click <a href="transfer.html"> Here. </a> </p>
				</article>
			</div>
			<div class="column" style="background-color:#ccc;">
			<h2>My Background</h2>
				<p>I'm a soccer fan who has followed the sport all my life. I grew up playing the game whenever I could, whether it be on a soccer field, my driveway, or on the street in front of my friends house. I primarily watch the Bundesliga as I support Bayern Munich. I do, however, tune into the Premier League, Serie A, and La Liga on a regular basis. </p>
